metadata.name: Magdalena
metadata.description:
Growing up Catholic I was always fascinated w/ religious mythology and iconography.

The prayers and experiences forever etched in my brain. The symbolisms sprinkled throughout my life in various times of fellowship.

In losing my mother, I was the closest I’ve been to death. Feeling her warmth leave her from my touch made me want to reconnect spiritually on a personal level, shedding sins and forgiving others. 

Magdalena speaks to finding grace in darkness.
